25namespace webrtc {
26
27std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> SupportedVP9Codecs() {
28#ifdef RTC_ENABLE_VP9
29 // Profile 2 might not be available on some platforms until
30 // https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webm/issues/detail?id=1544 is solved.
31 static bool vpx_supports_high_bit_depth =
32 (vpx_codec_get_caps(vpx_codec_vp9_cx()) & VPX_CODEC_CAP_HIGHBITDEPTH) !=
33 0 &&
34 (vpx_codec_get_caps(vpx_codec_vp9_dx()) & VPX_CODEC_CAP_HIGHBITDEPTH) !=
35 0;
36
37 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats{SdpVideoFormat(
38 cricket::kVp9CodecName,
39 {{kVP9FmtpProfileId, VP9ProfileToString(VP9Profile::kProfile0)}})};
40 if (vpx_supports_high_bit_depth) {
41 supported_formats.push_back(SdpVideoFormat(
42 cricket::kVp9CodecName,
43 {{kVP9FmtpProfileId, VP9ProfileToString(VP9Profile::kProfile2)}}));
44 }
45
46 return supported_formats;
47#else
48 return std::vector<SdpVideoFormat>();
49#endif
50}
51
52std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> SupportedVP9DecoderCodecs() {
53#ifdef RTC_ENABLE_VP9
54 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats = SupportedVP9Codecs();
55 // The WebRTC internal decoder supports VP9 profile 1. However, there's
56 // currently no way of sending VP9 profile 1 using the internal encoder.
57 // It would require extended support for I444, I422, and I440 buffers.
58 supported_formats.push_back(SdpVideoFormat(
59 cricket::kVp9CodecName,
60 {{kVP9FmtpProfileId, VP9ProfileToString(VP9Profile::kProfile1)}}));
61 return supported_formats;
62#else
63 return std::vector<SdpVideoFormat>();
64#endif
65}
66
67std::unique_ptr<VP9Encoder> VP9Encoder::Create() {
68#ifdef RTC_ENABLE_VP9
69 return std::make_unique<LibvpxVp9Encoder>(cricket::VideoCodec(),
70 LibvpxInterface::Create(),
71 FieldTrialBasedConfig());
72#else
73 RTC_NOTREACHED();
74 return nullptr;
75#endif
76}
77
78std::unique_ptr<VP9Encoder> VP9Encoder::Create(
79 const cricket::VideoCodec& codec) {
80#ifdef RTC_ENABLE_VP9
81 return std::make_unique<LibvpxVp9Encoder>(codec, LibvpxInterface::Create(),
82 FieldTrialBasedConfig());
83#else
84 RTC_NOTREACHED();
85 return nullptr;
86#endif
87}
88
89std::unique_ptr<VP9Decoder> VP9Decoder::Create() {
90#ifdef RTC_ENABLE_VP9
91 return std::make_unique<LibvpxVp9Decoder>();
92#else
93 RTC_NOTREACHED();
94 return nullptr;
95#endif
96}
